\[\forall\,(h,x,y)\in\mathcal{H}\times\mathcal{X}\times\mathcal{Y},\quad \widetilde{\mathsf{L}}_{\log}(h,x,y)=\sum_{y^{\prime}\in\mathcal{Y}}\bigl{(}1 -\overline{\mathsf{L}}(y^{\prime},y)\bigr{)}\log\Biggl{(}\sum_{y^{\prime\prime} \in\mathcal{Y}}e^{\sum_{i=1}^{l}\left(y_{i}^{\prime}-y_{i}^{\prime}\right)h(x,i )}\Biggr{)}.\] (17)

Here, \(\overline{\mathsf{L}}\) can be chosen as all the multi-label losses mentioned above. Next, we will show that \(\widetilde{\mathsf{L}}_{\log}\) benefits from \(\mathcal{H}\)-consistency bounds and Bayes consistency with respect to any of these loss functions.

