The proof of Theorem 5.1 is basically the same as that of Theorem 4.1, modulo replacing the Hamming loss \(\mathsf{L}_{\mathrm{ham}}\) with a general multi-label loss \(\mathsf{L}\). We include it in Appendix B.3 for completeness. When \(\mathcal{H}=\mathcal{H}_{\mathrm{all}}\), minimizability gaps \(\mathcal{M}_{\overline{\mathsf{L}}_{\log}}(\mathcal{H})\) and \(\mathcal{M}_{\mathsf{L}}(\mathcal{H})\) vanish, Theorem 4.1 implies excess error bound and Bayes-consistency of multi-label logistic loss with respect to any multi-label loss.

